comment_regular_data.body:
Hey @justinmk, I was able to dramatically simplify this. I had a fundamental misunderstanding of what was causing the assert to fail. I thought that the assert below was accessing the static `term_attrs[1024]` buffer directly but after looking deeper the `attrs` the assert was failing on in the ui_compositor is just derived from the static buffer. So if I just make sure we don't access garbage memory beyond that buffer the assert won't fail.

```
    for (int i = 0; i < endcol - startcol; i++) {
      assert(attrs[i] >= 0);
    }
```
